oman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes D'Umfravale was born in 1365, in Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir Thomas de Umfreville Of Rddesdale. She died on 25 October 1420, in Holmside, Durham, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1365–October 25, 1420":"1365–25. oktoober 1420","1361–1391":"1361–1391","1491–1535":"1491–1535","1365–1420":"1365–1420","1535":"1535","1365":"1365","1420":"1420","October 25, 1420":"25. oktoober 1420","1361":"1361","1491":"1491","1391":"1391","Holmside, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Holmside, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Castle, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1365–October 25, 1420":"1365–25. lokakuuta 1420","1361–1391":"1361–1391","1491–1535":"1491–1535","1365–1420":"1365–1420","1535":"1535","1365":"1365","1420":"1420","October 25, 1420":"25. lokakuuta 1420","1361":"1361","1491":"1491","1391":"1391","Holmside, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Holmside, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Castle, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1365–October 25, 1420":"1365–25 octobre 1420","1361–1391":"1361–1391","1491–1535":"1491–1535","1365–1420":"1365–1420","1535":"1535","1365":"1365","1420":"1420","October 25, 1420":"25 octobre 1420","1361":"1361","1491":"1491","1391":"13